Solution: The problem involves finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\), where \(Y_7\) is the seventh order statistic in a sample of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\). This means \(P(X \leq 27.3) = 0.7\), and since the distribution is continuous, \(P(X < 27.3) = 0.7\).

The event \(Y_7 < 27.3\) is equivalent to at least seven observations being less than 27.3. The number of observations less than 27.3 follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\). Thus, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(\text{Bin}(8, 0.7) \geq 7)\).

This probability is calculated as:
\[
P(B = 7) + P(B = 8) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 + \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8
\]
\[
