**************
The solution calculates the probability of a randomly selected person visiting a physical therapist as 0.68. This is obtained by setting up equations based on the given probabilities: 28% visit both a physical therapist and a chiropractor (\(P(A \cap C) = 0.28\)), 8% visit neither (\(P(\text{neither}) = 0.08\)), and the probability of visiting a physical therapist exceeds that of visiting a chiropractor by 16% (\(P(A) = P(C) + 0.16\)). Using the inclusion-exclusion principle and solving the equations, \(P(A) = 0.68\).

